	<Title>
		Recipe: Spinach berry salad
	</Title>
	<Abstract>
		Spinach berry salad &amp;mdash; one of many healthy recipes from Mayo Clinic.
	</Abstract>
	<ServingInfo Label="Serves">
		4
	</ServingInfo>
	<DietitianTip Label="Dietitian&apos;s tip" />
	<Directions Label="Directions">
		&lt;p&gt;
In a large salad bowl, toss together spinach, strawberries, blueberries, onion and pecans. In a jar with a tightfitting lid, combine dressing ingredients. Shake well. Pour over salad and toss to coat. Serve immediately. 
&lt;/p&gt;
	</Directions>
	<Ingredients Label="Ingredients">
		&lt;p&gt;
4 packed cups torn fresh spinach&lt;br /&gt;
1 cup sliced fresh strawberries&lt;br /&gt;
1 cup fresh, or frozen, blueberries&lt;br /&gt;
1 small sweet onion, sliced&lt;br /&gt;
1/4 cup chopped pecans, toasted&lt;br /&gt;
Salad Dressing&lt;br /&gt;
2 tablespoons white wine vinegar, or cider vinegar&lt;br /&gt;
2 tablespoons balsamic vinegar&lt;br /&gt;
2 tablespoons honey&lt;br /&gt;
2 teaspoons Dijon mustard&lt;br /&gt;
1 teaspoon curry powder (can be omitted)&lt;br /&gt;
1/8 teaspoon pepper 
&lt;/p&gt;
	</Ingredients>
